result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Waiver of time limits for preliminary hearing

records.addlTxt: 8:58 AM Defendant Dale D Ahonen in court.  Attorney Heidi E. Brewer in court for Dale D Ahonen.  Prosecuting attorney Matthew J Tingstad in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 22CF51, 22CM44, 22CM66.  22CM44, Def waives formal reading of complaint.  Reserves juris challenges.  Stands mute.  Clerk to enter NG plea.  PTC 10/12 at 9:15 a.m.  22CM66, Court reiterates charges.  Atty Brewer waives formal reading of complaint, Reserves juris challenges.  Stands mute.  NG to be entered by Clerk.  PTC for 10/12 at 9:15 a.m.  22CF51, Court reiterates charges.  Atty Brewer has gone through complaint with def.  Waives formal reading.  Reserves juris challenges and waives time limits for prelim.  Case set for PTC on 10/12 at 9:15.  Bond continues.  Court addresses def.  Adj.  9:30 a.m.  klr

records.descr: Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant

records.addlTxt: Def shall speak with intake worker at  DHS for mental health services. Def cannot go to property/home on (location redacted)

2:00 p.m.  Court calls case, cites appearances.  Def appears in person, in custody.  DA appears in person.  Court reiterates charges.  Def provided copy of complaint.  Def advised of right to atty.  Def provides statements to court.  Court advises def to prelim right.  Def unsure about waiver of time limit for prelim.  Court advises of right to atty again.  DA requests bond requirement that keeps def away from a certain property to be provided.  $500 cash bond requested.  Can do initial app next week.  Def states cannot post cash.  Def indicates he can post on Friday.  Court explains what bond is for.  Def states had permission to be on premises.  Court explains not here to try case at this time.  Court questions def re mental health evaluation.  Court questions Sheriff can help make arrangements for def to see mental health intake worker.  Court sets signature bond of $1,000.  Def shall speak with DHS for mental health services and def cannot go to property/home on U.S. 51, (location known to def., 12521 U.S. Hwy 51, Carey).  Initial app to be set.  Prelim to be set within 20 days and AIA 9/19 at 10:30 a.m.  Def does not have an address at this time.  Def has provided documentation to be filed with the court.  Adj.  2:14 p.m.  klr
